title: The Colours of a Dream
author: natalie
text: i lay on the beach not a sound for a mile,  in this breath taking dream all i can do is smile.   i can sense the sweet air,  there is no room for complaint,  in the distance an image but,  oh so faint.   i ponder about this newly found place,  but no given time or location and mask over face.   in this world iâ’m head,  no restriction,  no rule,  the climate is perfect not to warm,  nor to cool.   i dread when itâ’s time to leave this land,  but youâ’ll know iâ’ve been here from the steps in the sand.   no one can tell when iâ’ll come back or leave,   it may be morn,  afternoon or even late eve.   iâ’ve said my good-byes,  there is nowhere else to go,  i would love to stay longer but i must say no.   the time has come; i have woken from my sleep,   the fun i had,  made memories to forever keep.

title: Unleashed
author: nathan
text: unleashed i just wanted to let you know that i love you.  and i wanted to know do you love me too.  i will love you no matter what you do.  i don't care what the stake.  i just dont want you to be fake.  i want you to love me for me.  i want you to love me when i am all i can be.  i want you to be there when i am in the pits.  i want to be there when you throw a fit.  i want everything to be everything.  i dont want it to be anything.  i wouldnt care if you were all i had.  then i really wouldn't be that sad.  i want our love to be sweet.  i want our love to rhyme to a beat.  i want to be able to accomplish impossible feats.  i know that it isnt easy.  i dont like love when its cheesey.  i dont like it when you cry.  i dont like to have to say good bye.  i guess its okay to let out some sighs.  i don't like it when i shed a tear.  i know i can wash away all of your fears.  since you been gone it aint the same.  i drop a tear when i hear your name.  i like it when our love feels new.  i know i only like a few.  i want your love to be released.  i want your love to be unleashed!!!

text: as the path reaches up to grab me,  i push myself to run faster.                               as the cold rain pushes me down towards hell,  i do not fill well.                                 i see i am almost to the finish line,  and first place will be mine.                                      i go down a hill and pick up as much speed as i can.                                                   there is just a few more feet to go.                              i pass the finish line first and fall to the ground exhausted and excited.                       out of breath i meet my coach at the finish line,  and she is over joyed that i won.                                               i will remember this moment the rest of my life.                        i was a member of a great cross x country team that i am proud to have been on.                       then the sun comes out,  birds start chirping,  and a smile and peace comes over me.              when my team is together we will go for a cool down run at a slow pace and talk about the race.

title: Bat or Mouse
author: nathan
text: by day the bat is cousin to the mouse.  he likes the attic of an aging house.  his fingers make a hat about his head.  his pulse beat is so slow we think him dead.  he loops in crazy figures half the night among the trees that face the corner light.  but when he brushes up against a window,   we are afraid of what our eyes have seen: for something is amiss or out of place when mice with wings can wear a human face.

title: Before She Died
author: nathan
text: when i look at the sky now,  i look at it for you.  as if with enough attention,  i could take it in for you.  with all the leaves gone almost from the trees,  i did not walk briskly through the field.  late today with my dog wool,  i lay down in the upper field,  he panting and aged,  me looking at the blue.  leaning on him,  i wondered how finite these lustered days seem to you,  a stand of hemlock across the lake catches my eye.  it will take a long time to know how it is for you.  like a dog's lifetime â— long â— multiplied by sevens.

title: Passion of love

title: Thee to my love
author: nathan
text: how do i love thee? let me count the ways.  i love thee to the depth and breadth and height my soul can reach,  when feeling out of sight for the ends of being and ideal grace.  i love thee to the level of every day's most quiet need,  by sun and candlelight.  i love thee freely,  as men strive for right; i love thee purely,  as they turn from praise.  i love thee with the passion put to use in my old grief,  and with my childhood's faith.  i love thee with a love i seemed to lose with my lost saints, â—i love thee with the breath,  smiles,  tears,  of all my life!â—and,  if god choose,  i shall but love thee better after death.

title: Not a poem
author: nathan
text: \ti wish i had integrity.  integrity is not just being truthful while people's backs are turned; it's doing the right thing all the time.  it is telling the truth.  it is being helpful.  it is respecting yourself and others.  that is only a few steps to having integrity.  \tintegrity is to be free of people watching you every second of your life.  my scout master mr.  negron has a business called integron.  integron stands for integrity,  and negron.  he put those two words together and it meant that his business has integrity.  he has told me that not everyone is perfect,  but everyone has to have a little integrity.  he asked me if i had integrity but i could not answer.  that is why i need integrity.  without integrity this world would be a mess.  i for one i am trying to have integrity.  with your heart,  your mind,  and someone's help you can work on having integrity.    \ti plan on pushing out those bad habits,  impulses,  bad ideas,  schemes,  and any other thing that i do in my life.  some steps in having integrity would be to focus on school work,  chores,  following rules,  being nice,  and paying attention every day.  it will be hard but i know i can do it.  it takes a lot of effort doing things the right way,  but when you do the things in the right way you feel good.  i have to stop lying to everybody and tell the truth so i can do fun things,  and hang out with friends,  and not stay home moping in my room.  it will be worth all the effort.  \thaving integrity is a big thing in life.  many people don't know this.  it keeps life balanced along with a lot of other things.  i will have integrity soon.  it will be in my life until in die.  you do not need bold words,  or a good heart to have integrity.  all you really need is to be truthful,  helpful,  happy,  and respect others.  then your life is better than ever.  \ta person that has integrity helps others.  the one thing that you need to do in order to have integrity is believe in yourself.   integrity means lots of things not just one.  it means being truthful,  brave,  friendly,  kind,  thrifty,  and clean minded.   like i said before (integrity is not just being truthful while people's backs are turned; it's doing the right thing all the time. ) so do what's right,  make a spot in your life for integrity.

title: Buzzer Beater
author: nicholas
text: i sit on the bench,  during the second half while waldon middle school is slowly pulling away.  i look on as we fall down by 15.    then i hear the call â“nicholasâ” from the other end,  of the bench.  i run down and kneel by the scorekeeper.  i enter at the next dead ball.  3 minutes left.    i am getting more playing time,  than i usually get.    i come and make two jump shots from the corner.    we go back and forth until we are down by 8.    i glance at the clock 4 seconds left.  i grab the inbounds pass out of the air and explode.  dribbling with my right hand                                                                                             i rush past my defender                                                                                                 the crowd screams i cross half court when the clock hits 2.  i put the ball on my right shoulder.    with one second remaining i heave it.    the ball is soaring through the air in a high arc,  just to the right of the basket.  it is not going to go in.    the buzzer sounds and the ball keeps going.  the gym goes quiet.  the ball softly kisses off the glass and swishes through the basket.  out of the corner of my eyes.  i see fans clad in clarkston colors rise to their feet and cheer.

title: Earthquake
author: paige
text: up in the tibetan mountains is where i live in the town of qinghai.  the ground often shakes in this mountainous land.  but we stay, we live, we love.   six in less then three hours.  this must be a record we sit cuddled around the t. v just watching and waiting in deathly silence  the quake hits at 7:49 some are still asleep but wake up soon enough.  this is like no other.   we flee from our home as all around us mud and wood buildings crumble.  mud slides down the road ahead as my parents flee  i stand still.   there is something not right about fleeing i dissapear into the rubble hoping to be safe praying for my friends and family who sickening screams i can hear.   the screaming stops and all falls silent i pop out and look around to find destruction.   injured bodies and ruined homes downed phone lines but the worst of all the top of the buddist temple lies heavy on the ground before me.   men in uniform arrive within hours carrying blankets and tents but behind the good is the bad,  strechers for the dead and wounded.   i grab a blanket and a tent and watch the men as they work carrying out the dead and helping the living.   a few days later efforts are still strong when i see a soilder walk up to me with dad's hat in his arms.   his voice is booming as he says holding up a picture

title: The Bird On My Head

text: i awoke one morning to find perched upon my head a bird as white as the glistening snow.  â“why are you here?â”i asked once he noticed i was there the snow white bird gave me a long stare.  he then opened humongous beak and screeched  â“ i am here on a mission.  to show mankind what they have done,  to this beautiful planet and all thatâ’s in it.  and i think you might be the one to help me.  go out and spread the word to the people.  that earth is precious,  generous and kind and it should never be destroyed.   show them pictures of the animals the snow white planes and everlasting blue skies.  show them a mother gorilla cradling her cute baby,  show them the great blue whales of the deep.  show them that earth is beautiful.  show them that not everything is worth claiming and what is mine is also yours.   tell them about the rain forest filled with mystery and mystique,  tell them about the mountains that are so high you can barely see the peaks  then once you are done telling the people in you town go to the next  and then the next.  and go until there is no town left untouched by the words you speak.  and then after you go to every town make sure those bulldozers hear it and the companies here it because earth is valuable not in the money since,  but in itâ’s own way. â”  then with one last squawk the glistening white bird flew off and i hoped out of bed and ran to the town square and yelled to the heavens what i had just heard from the glistening white bird that sat on top of my head.

title: Euphoria
author: randi
text: i sit, trombone in hand. voices murmur around me, speaking of us, the band. speaking of how we sound, of how we look. the director walks out onto the stage. silence. the band stands as one. the director bows at the crowds applause. he turns. all but three band members sit down. i am one of them. the trombones. tonight, for one song, we are special. we navigate around stands to walk to the front. my smile threatens to break my face. this is it. here we go. we, stand, instruments ready, waiting for the cue to bring them to the playing position. the director raises the conductor's baton. the cue. my heart pounds. i bring my trombone to my mouth, ready to play when my time comes. the director shows the tempo with minute flicks of the baton. the he swings his arms, pointing. the band plays. the trombones come in, loud and clear. we play together, in time, right notes, right rhythms. perfection. euphoria. ecstasy. the song ends. the band stands. we all bow. the director points at the trombone players. the cheering gets louder. some stand. more get up. we got a standing ovation. i smile. my smile gets wider and wider. until. . . crack! my face breaks.

title: Loud minds
author: rhea
text: i sit in the silence of the room,  but not in my mind   i hide and cover myself with the pain when the pressure rains down on me like a thousand needles   that is when i walk down a path of empty promises and no destination   that road that led nowhere held by lingering souls who pay tolls of loneliness   i wonder,  why is my mind so loud in such a quiet room,  why do i hide and become shy?   i am consumed by my own feelings,  but they still look at me with contempt in their eyes    looking at me thinking i can't do anything,  it's not true i just choose   i am not a helpless mouse haunted by the thoughts of the wild   i don't spin around in question,  hoping for the worse one day,  yet i don't wish for the best to come   those who are held back by their past and dreams blame that one reason without surpassing    the purpose is not to surpass your friends,  family,  dreams,  or foes,  but yourself   to surpass yourself means to walk along that path until the end comes near   until then you and i will be chased,  running down that road hand in hand with loneliness,  anxiety,  fear,  and the nasty things you say to yourself   it is not all dark,  but a shimmer of sunlight leaks into the dark black jar i sit in   i wish to seek all brightness,  to lay in the grass with another whom i trust,  but these are just fantasies i absently wish for   laying on the grassy green hill in my dreams waiting for my loyal friend to lay beside me,  sleeping in bliss,  i will miss my dreams,  my imagination,  and i will dry up into the air along with my thought of tranquility   that day will be the end,  i will fill with fake smiles,  shattered laughs,  and a stone cold face   with no emotions,  i will cause no commotions for others to enjoy    i will fill with pressure,  i am a thousand pounds heavier,  but i know it is just my imagination   that is my road led to the back of my mind that goes throughout my simple life    this is what my mind carries,  holds,  and protects   how controlling minds can be crowding your head with words full of worries

text: when i awoke one morning,   a stork was on my head.  i asked,  ''what are you doing there?''  it looked at me and said .  .  .   â“as you lay there in your bed,  the night is turning into day,  and as you lie there with all your troubles tucked away,  someone out there is in need of a friend.  they may be red,  yellow,  black,  or white,  but you should never judge a book by its cover.  you should be accepting enough to look inside  and see the person behind the mask.   no matter how ugly someone may seem at first,  everyone can change no matter what the odds.  but beware there are those that will try to take advantage of you.  they can be changed with a little love and should be treated like anyone else.  so remember this as the world turns,  so does time,  and as time turns the dark into day,  someone is in need of a friend.  take my advice and be nice,  take a slice out of life and make a friend!

title: I Am

text: i am a hilarious and comical guy.  i wonder what the upcoming future holds for the world.  i hear the desolate cry of the winds of change.  i see the gateway of time,  which the world is destined to enter.  i want time to slow down,  so i can enjoy life.  i am a hilarious and comical guy.   i pretend i am testing my wits in competition.  i feel the pressure of my superiors.  i touch the barrier that prevents me from changing.  i worry about the futureâ’s destruction.  i cry for those who fail to proceed in life.  i am a hilarious and comical guy.   i understand the hardships experienced in life.  i say that one deserves what he aspires for.  i dream of peaceful worldwide change.  i try to reach my deepest desires through my abilities.  i hope i can complete graduation and move on.  i am a hilarious and comical guy.

title: Lust

text: a wolf howles in the night.  the wind whistles through the air,  and tangles feebly in my hair.  no stars in the midnight sky.  the great moon hides behind the frame of a large oak tree.  an owl asks who is there,  and answers only an eco of a deep cave.  i take a step forward.  the mud squishes under my bare foot,  sending an oze through my toes.  i shiver,  but not from the cold.  now i only hear the erratic beating in my chest like drums.  blood is pulsing through my veins,  thirsting the hunter.  i grip my knife.  blood is still ozing down my face,  my hands,  my chest.  i am glazed in a thin layer of not only my blood but others too.  i take a deep breath,  and step forward. . .  a wolf howles in the night.

text: life is a collection of moments and memories we experience happiness and joy to sadness and sorrow  our greatest fears are tested and our strengths are shown through triumphs and losses will we know who we are tomorrow  adversities and obstacles may stand in our way but overcoming them may lead to the greatest gift of all  many people have their own idea on what life truly is whether they define it as risk takers or people who just live by their own rules in the end though,  weâ’re most impacted by our decisions decisions we make everyday affect how we live and what we do there are role models and there are criminals  they're polar opposites,  but yet are still who they are for their choices  life is a mixture of everything imaginable  from our victories and losses to our joy and sadness with friends and loved ones to share these moments with life gives us many gifts along with hardships but with the greatest treasure of them all  is knowing that we ourselves are one of the biggest influences on who we are  we create our future

''brother, brother,  are you alright? will you still stand?'' said the other.   ''no brother,  i am afraid i am not well at all,  i will not be able to stand much longer,  for i feel my base crumbling,  and i fear that i am bound to fall. ''  and then the brother crumbled and fell,  with his dying breath,  he said, '' brother, be careful,  i see another bird from hell''  the last standing brother looked in all directions,  but the bird could'nt be seen.  for his brother's dust,  and smoke had created a blinding screen.   his brother's falling,  crumbling,  tumbling debris went on as an avalanche quickly following the running people,   all but the firemen and police officers,  for they had runshed into the courageous decree.   antoher bird dropped down,  ready for a suicidal attack.  the brother,  cringed with fear and anger as he braced for the impact.   kaboom! kaboom! the expolsion was as loud as the first.  at this,  the people yelled and cursed.   ms.  liberty weeped tears of saddness for the brothers' soul.  just then,  the patriot uncle sam rose from the brothers' bodies,  pulled up his sleeve,  wiped a tear and said,  ''let's roll. title: What it Takes
author: sarah
text: do you have what it takes? not to be great,  not to be famous,  not completing some death defying act just being yourself and making the best use of your talents to help someone.   you don't have to be funny     or       fascinating                  or                    fabulous     to make a difference in this world.             you can be silent             and make a big             difference in             this world. you             can shout it  from the mountaintop or keep it safely stored away inside your head.  it can be shared in deeds rather than words. just a gentle touch or soothing hand or quiet courage and unfailing love are what is              needed today.               so do not wait              or withhold,  but              wait for the               right moment.               and reach out              your hand- do         you have what it takes?

title: Story of My Life

text: i thought they know i loved them,  i thought they loved me too.  they didnâ’t listen to a word i said,  for them maybe,  i was dead.  i hate this night and i hate this day,  i wish i could just fly away.  my life is no good than hell someoneâ’s got explanations to tell.  they said dear ones are what you lived for,   well,  they are the reason i donâ’t want to live anymore.   they made me choke and they made me sigh.  i still gave it a try.  i worked by day and worked by night.  on that,  they never laid their sight.  every step i took to make my life bright.  they stopped it with all their might.  on the death bed,  my hopes did lay,  i wish i could just fly away.  tears had flooded my eyes.  i still tried my best to be nice.  ……………………………………………….  my dad; i was his biggest fan.  for me,  he was my superman.  my mom; how much she was loved by me,  no words could tell,  no eyes could see.  even my life had good moments.  but i donâ’t know where they went.  i died inside,  every single day,  i wish i could just fly away.

title: Droplets of Agony
author: savannah
text: they drip from the pane to the sill,  in hopes that they can get there,  they will.  they race each other to see who'll win the prize,  and we sit and watch with adoring eyes.  when they hit the sill they gasp for air,  but most who are watching,  don't care.  they aren't interesting when they aren't in action, people who are watching have a subtle reaction.  they forget about that drop of rain,  that slid gracefully down the window pane.  as it lies screaming,  evaporating into the surrounding atmosphere,  the only people who are around,  don't hear.

title: Stroke
author: shaelynn

title: Took all my life
author: shima
text: i was five,  full of life,  happiness,  joy and delight.  there came a mighty storm late at night,  twisted around my childhood dreams,  took my happiness,  and took my life.  grabbed my joy,  killed my bunny,  ruined my wooden house,  and knocked down the slide.  i had a little bike; my feet were little,  still would not reach the ground,  before mounting every day,  i would measure my height,   hoping to grow before it was night,  as i had to go to bed to get ready for yet another ride.  in the dreams,  i had,  my legs where long,  they could reach the paddle and ride on the cloud,  i would then happily yell and feel the pride.  all has now disappeared at a glance! the dreams vanished,  the clouds turned black.  the color of the blue sky also changed all at once.  back to the ground,  i do not find my bike; i only see the bunny who shared the ride.  the bunny is wounded and bleeding so hard.  i ran to my mother,  mother was dazed and horrified.  she looked at the bunny,  and said it has died.  i buried it in the garden with a broken part of my heart.  my heart is now shattered,  its missing some parts,  the bunny took one; i had already given a piece to the cloud,  it used to draw me lambs,  when it was all white,  but when changed color,  it broke my heart.  i was only five,  my heart made out of glass,  it pounded so easy when touched the ground.  now i am in late thirties,  my heart still cries,  it is not glass anymore,  it turned into scrap,  though still pounds when senses something harsh.  my daughter is growing; she turned five last night.  the cold is approaching and i fear the storms.  its memory engraved in my soul and mind and many traces of it still found.  i am alert and cautious but the storm is so tough.  i am building an iron fence around her heart to fight the storm no matter how hard.  i hope i manage before time runs out.

title: IN A WORLD OF FOOLS
author: shira
text: woe to the lovers,  dreamers,  and fools,  the ones who have tampered with logical rules.  they want what they know they canâ’t get,  and when they finally get it,  it comes with regret.  they complicate what should have been easy,  they decide to make your stomach flip and make you queasy.  they make so many tears form,  the tears they shed come out as a storm.    but to my sorrow and grief i have becomes one among the rest,  i have fallen to the power that conquers me,  even though i have tried not to fail this test.    why must my heart be so stubborn with me,  it blinds my emotions until i cannot even see.  it deceives my mind and turns it astray,  and that is why so many days of mine seam gray.  the tearing noise is the splitting of my heart,   mercilessly i have watched and even helped it be ripped apart.   my body is splitting; heart and mind,  and my true self i cannot seam find.  i no longer have the sense of feel,  my heart is undecided to what i may accept as real.  itâ’s scary to have no control over myself,  my life has turned to a mere storybook sitting on a dusty old shelf.   i donâ’t know where i have gone or when iâ’ll be back,  but i will only return if i do not get my mind or heart attacked.   all emotion is blocked out,  and not even my voice is left to shout.   there is something raging inside of me,   i want to let go,  but somehow my spirit is not yet free.  in a cage they call body i am trapped,  my spirit remains restless while my body napped.  my feet want to carry me away,  but they donâ’t know where,  my eyes want to let me see a different view,  but in only one direction can i stare.  the spirits that bind my heart and my mind,  have left my whole body; leaving a lost soul behind.  i have sunken into the ground which bore me life; i have sunken deep inside,  the ground had too many expectations of me that i had to hide.  and now i can only pray,  that tomorrow will be a different day.

title: Power
author: siddharh
text: i am the reason,  why? why the world thrives,  i am love,  i am harsh,  you have seen my affection,  but you are yet to see my exasperation.    if i have made you grin like the cheshire cat,  i can make you snivel out blood from your eyes,  if i let you control the world,  i can even take it back,  i can crush it and be its queen,    and if i had a helping hand,  it would mean a straight way up,  but that does not mean i am not going to toil and moil,  i am going to give my best,  and prove who i am,  it may be you,  you,  or even you,  cause if i see even the slightest light,  i can change the world and make it mine,  a better place as i am the mother,  i am the one,  who knows the best,  and can notice what my child needs,  to wait on someoneâ’s hand and foot,  and castigate it when it takes a wrong step.    today the world has evolved in its own ways,  with people now going their separate ways,  making expressions with no reactions,  as they wish to stay this way,  we need to get our own lighter and luminescence the way.    we have the potential to grow,  the capability to hold the nation together,  a prorogation to have power,  and vagueness to lead,  we do not need to get a chance we make our own chance,  to prove to others we are the one,  and we have the right and ability to show the world,  we can and we will be empowered with or without your help,  and start a new era of women empowerment!

title: Taken
author: stephanie
text: there are days when i don't wanna get out of my bed,  when the voices are raging inside of my head.  my stomach is turning and tied in knots,  and my mind is filled with all sorts of thoughts.  i can't understand why i'm feeling like this,  there must be a part of my life that i miss.  was it that one boy who was my only true love,  but was suddenly stolen and sent up above? or maybe that girl who was my best friend of all,  but then she left without even a call.  it seems like everything i had was taken,  and as i lay here thinking,  my heart is breaking.  maybe it is meant for me to live my life alone,  and to suffer and to cry about the ones i used to know.  well now i'm moving on without the others that have past,  to live my life in happiness with the memories that will last.

title: A Poem about Me

text: i am a girl with blue/green eyes        in the summer i like to fly i have brown hair with blonde highlights  at  night i go into sleeping twilight            i'm 5'7 inches tall        and i like to play basketball            i like to watch occ       and spend time with my family         i love to go to the mall  my least favorite season of all is fall

title: A summer's breeze...
author: stephanie
text: i woke up this morning,  and you were then first thing on my mind.   i walked around for hours,  with a smile on my face,  due to the picture of you i had in my mind.   i don't know where it came from,  or why for that matter,  all that i know is that i need you in my life.   when i am with you,  i feel as if i can grow to become a better woman.   can i walk with you,  at the right hand of god?  can it be possible,  that i am destined,  to be with you?  can i be your friend,  until the end?  you have be wondering,  if you know how i feel about you.   these feelings are so strong,  i cannot imagine,  that you do not feel them too.   you have known me long enough,  to know that you can trust me,  with your heart.   everyday is like a summer's day,  when i am with you,  the sun shines brighter,  all around.   the summer's breeze,  reaches us all,  and fills me,  with sweet memories of you.   it carries your special fragrance,  a temptation,  that is all too sweet.

title: Hopefully...
author: stephanie
text: hopefully. . .   i am in pain.  unbearable,  unforgettable pain.   i cannot stop him,  for it is not my nature,  i want to feel happy for him,  but i cannot.   i feel unwarranted hatred towards her,  she who has come here,  and taken away everything that i wanted.  always she has,  and now i feel hurt.  but i call her friend.   i know that she doent not feel for him as i do.  but she will have him,  she will have once again,  what i want.   he will make the decision,  that i would love for him not to make,  and he will end up with heartache.   but in the end,  i will be here,  i will be here to help him through the pain,  through the pain that i feel right now,  and then i shall have him,  he shall be mine. . .  hopefully.

title: I tell myself...
author: stephanie
text: i tell myself…  i tell myself no,  that i shouldnâ’t even think about him.   but he clouds up my mind,  with unmentionable thoughts  i tell myself no,  that asking him out will only cause hurt.  but every time i speak to him,  i have to fight the urge to say the unspeakable words  i tell myself no,  that he would never accept me,  that i am not his type.   i tell myself to look away,  when i see him look at others.   i tell myself that it is okay,  that he never looks to me like that.   i tell myself not to care,  to ignore the hurt i feel deep inside.   i tell myself,  that these feeling are nothing,  that they will go away.  i tell myself i am too young,  too young to truly care for anyone.   i tell myself,  to move on,  that it is time,  time to move onto the next.   i tell myself all of these things,  to make myself immune.  to stop the emotions i feel inside,  from growing anymore.   but they are here,  and for a time they shall stay.   so i tell myself,  to stay strong,  to live another day,   and to let life take its course,  to love each day to the fullest.

title: Fire

title: What it takes to forgive
author: stone
text: dear bullies and oppressors,    i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after the blood of your victims form into a tsunami and boils with rage,  inflicting the damage caused by your torment two-fold  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after each night when you sleep you experience a glimpse of their hopelessness and suffering for a short time in your dreams constantly haunting you until you stop your twisted ways  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after you branch off from the terror you have delivered and plant a new sapling to replace the mighty tree you sawed down,  each tooth of the chain a vicious assault on their psychological well being,  powered by your insecurities and controlled by their helplessness,  and feed the sapling with positivity as it shines like light,  compliments that fluidly roll off your tongue cultivating and helping to grow the sapling,  and using friendship to act like soil,  to make a sturdy foundation for the roots to grasp and strive with  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after you have gone door by door and let your victims spit on you like you did to them,  let them taunt you like you did to them,  and let them hurt you like the way you did until the rage is gone and the wounds can heal,  the release of their stress like a valve being opened and healing waters allowed to flow freely into their minds  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after you feel the same hopelessness of your victims not by walking a mile in their shoes,  no,  by walking around the equator of this planet,  each new place like a new type of torment,  and once you have worn those shoes maybe then will i forgive you  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after you are forced to have insults shoved down your throat each day and forced to taste the acidic,  bitter,  and hot taste of them as they are forced,  giving you a glimpse of the agony your victims suffer  i am told by many of you that i must forgive and so i shall  after you go through everything i have said and manage to come out changed for the better,  once you can sympathise with your victimâ’s pain and can say with a straight face you were wrong,  once you give the first hug and experience the joy of building with love and compassion instead of destroying all around you with your toxic tongue capable of melting diamonds,  once you breathe life into people instead of take it,  then i will forgive,  but will never forget sincerely,  stone b.

title: I Remember, I Remember
author: subin
text: i remember,  i remember  those young times of life  when innocent faces floated  free of all sins.   i remember,  i remember  those tension free times of life i enjoyed oblivious of my duties.   i remember,  i remember  gazing at the vast skies perplexed and oblivious of what i was peering at.   i remember,  i remember  napping all the time dreaming in a world of games  and fun in my tottering cradle.   i remember,  i remember  those scary nights of life filled with my hallucinations of wraiths and fiends.   i remember,  i remember  crying not of grief but of hunger and when i want to see my parents.   i remember,  i remember  those times of life when i was a helpless infant  baffled by all i saw.   i remember,  i remember  all of my feline friends but what have we become now? just monsters in a feline shape.  i remember,  i remember  my first day at school when i was afraid  to leave my parents.   i remember,  i remember  my first lessons in life which started my voyage into the endless sea of knowledge.   i remember,  i remember  those never ending memories that keeps coming to my mind as if they have eternal life.   i remember,  i remember  my first vow to my country to help it develop and to stand with it always.   i remember,  i remember  my first walking lessons when i was delighted by my achievements.   i remember,  i remember  munching on tasty treats eating tasty fruits  but hating vegetables.   i remember,  i remember looking up at everyone engulfed in thoughts asking â“when will i grow tall?â”  i remember,  i remember those innocent times of life when i never felt any grudge but just loved everyone.  i remember,  i remember the foolish dreams i had of ruling the world and of  becoming the best.    i remember,  i remember my treasured parents who care  and work hard all day for my bright future.   i remember,  i remember those worthy times of life circling in my mind like the water in a fountain.   i remember,  i remember those young times of life when innocent faces floated free of all sins.

title: A New Crayon Box
author: sue
text: yellow?  purple?  red?  blue? green? one would think god would be mad at crayon makers: with boxes of 12,  25 or 32,  broken or whole - paper bound or peeled bare.   with sharpeners that worry the stick and children who melt them,  or eat them,  or stick them up their noses.   just look at spring and fall,  winter and summer greens.   look at skin and fur and hair and eyes.   there are more than even the big box of 64!   i think god wants us to have crayon boxes that have 1000 greens and more than double that blues.   and even black comes in more than one color in my world.   so does white and down and up and lonely and sad.   i think colors are god's way of saying ''hello down there!  pay attention!  look what ya got!''  this box of colors ain't goin' in no school desk!

title: Earth's Requiem
author: teresa
text: the destruction of my home began a long time ago.  who can stop them?my friends have long gone. they have taken my family too - mother father brothers sisters love sons daughters.   i tried to protect them all, but in the end i failed each one. i am the only one left.  the trees cry out as they die,  but you cannot hear them.  i lie here,  neither dead nor alive,  listening to the pain of the forest and feeling the ache in my heart.  the earth is crying.  she nurtured them.  why are they killing their true mother? i am alone. my only comfort is the thought that they'll find me soon -  because when they do, this misery will finally end. i'll be ready to see my loved ones again. but,  until then,  i will endure these bleeding wounds within me and continue drowning in earth's tears.

title: Rain's Race.
author: tiara
text: the rain hops from the clouds down into the large crowds.   children laugh and they play,  but today is not my day.   no sun?  no fun.   i'd rather it be sunny and bright,   not gloomy and the sky looking like night.  i watch two droplets race down the window pane,   the larger one's riding the gravity train,   while the smaller one it's slow but not steady,   i wish it'd hurry up already.

title: Racing droplets
author: tiara
text: the rain hops from the clouds  down to the large crowds.   children laugh,  children play,   but today is not my day.   no sun? no fun.  i watch two droplets race down the window pane,  the larger one riding the gravity train.   the smaller one,  slow but unsteady.  i wish it'd hurry up already.  they soon come together as one,   so neither of them have won.

title: Music Changes Lives
author: tina
text: once upon a long ago time,  a man committed a modest crime.  he knew he'd be imprisoned for what he did,  the man was afraid,  and so he hid.   after a while he was filled with guilt,  for what he had done; he knew he'd wilt.  then suddenly the man heard a sweet,  soft tune,  it was as glorious as the midnight moon.   drops of tears fell out of his eyes,  his heart lifted,  and soared to the skies.  for the music was filled with comfort and love,  it symbolized the peace of a lovely dove.   soon the man turned himself in,  he went to prison for his minor sin.  a few months later,  he was let out,  a feeling of excitement made him shout.   meanwhile,  a war of hatred was going on,  suddenly the man remembered the beautiful song.  he arranged for a choir to sing the tune,  and his conscience told him the war would end soon.  the kings of both countries soon heard the song,  their bitter hearts softened and they hummed along.  and this was how the fighting came to an end,  and soon the kings became quite good friends. .   epilogue: if you are sad,  remember this,  music brings happiness,  and lots of bliss.  so just whistle along or sing any tune,  and you will feel better very soon.
